<subSubSection id="3BE6651EF67A8D0FFF139DCDFACCFED2" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="73433695F67A8D0FFF139DCDFAA2FFD6" blockId="15.[151,1437,1717,2033]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFF139DCDFEF7FFF2" bold="true" box="[151,261,1717,1744]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Material.</emphasis>
Assigned specimens 
<collectionCode id="15EDAE50F67A8D0FFE689DCEFDEBFFF2" box="[492,537,1718,1744]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/fx78-973d" name="The University of Iowa (formerly State University of Iowa)" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="University or college">SUI</collectionCode>
147587–147594, from Section MME 36.4m, Fillmore Formation (upper Tremadocian; Stairsian; 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D16F67A8D0FFEC09DA3FDB3FFD7" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" box="[324,577,1754,1781]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Rossaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leboni">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFEC09DA3FE0FFFD6" box="[324,509,1754,1780]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Rossaspis leboni</emphasis>
Zone
</taxonomicName>
), southern Confusion Range, Ibex area, Millard County, western 
<collectingRegion id="B138F877F67A8D0FFA979DA2FABEFFD6" box="[1299,1356,1754,1780]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Utah</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73433695F67A8D0FFF439D85FACCFED2" blockId="15.[151,1437,1717,2033]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFF439D85FEBEFE3A" bold="true" box="[199,332,1789,1816]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Discussion.</emphasis>
Specimens retrieved from Section MME 36.4 m are from lower in the same zone as those of 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D16F67A8D0FFA0C9D87FEF7FE1E" authorityName="Adrain &amp; Karim" authorityYear="2019" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Tesselacauda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morrisoni">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFA0C9D87FEF7FE1E" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">T. morrisoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sample from MME 36.4 m is in general fragmentary and sparse, but most species seem to occur also in the assemblage at MME 49.8 m. The 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D16F67A8D0FFDD09C3EFD18FE42" authorityName="Ross" authorityYear="1951" box="[596,746,1862,1888]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Tesselacauda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFDD09C3EFD18FE42" box="[596,746,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Tesselacauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens, however, definitely do not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D16F67A8D0FFA889C3FFA67FE42" authorityName="Adrain &amp; Karim" authorityYear="2019" box="[1292,1429,1863,1888]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Tesselacauda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morrisoni">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFA889C3FFA67FE42" box="[1292,1429,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">T. morrisoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dorsal pygidial surfaces of most specimens are almost completely effaced, and lack the clusters of tubercles on the distal parts of the pleurae which characterize 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D16F67A8D0FFD3C9CF7FCB3FE8A" authorityName="Adrain &amp; Karim" authorityYear="2019" box="[696,833,1935,1960]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Tesselacauda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morrisoni">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFD3C9CF7FCB3FE8A" box="[696,833,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">T. morrisoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The terminal piece, while relatively large, is about as wide as it is long, whereas those of pygidia of 
<taxonomicName id="B4FC4D16F67A8D0FFD279CCBFCDFFEEE" authorityName="Adrain &amp; Karim" authorityYear="2019" box="[675,813,1971,1996]" class="Trilobita" family="Pliomeridae" genus="Tesselacauda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morrisoni">
<emphasis id="4188EA87F67A8D0FFD279CCBFCDFFEEE" box="[675,813,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">T. morrisoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much longer than wide. The MME 36.4 m material seems to represent a poorly known but distinct species, the oldest member of the genus thus far recovered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
